{
  "texts": [
    "A useful approximation of transaction cost that takes market impact into account is",
    "where the first term is the bid-ask spread component of transaction cost, and the second models the market impact, i.e., the additional cost incurred as the trade eats through the order book.",
    "The vector κ impact has positive entries and typically takes the form",
    ", where s i is the volatility of asset i over the trading period, v i is the volume of market trading, expressed as a multiple of the portfolio value, and a is a constant on the order of one; see [GK00, Loe83",
    ", TLD + 11, MTB14] and [BBD + 17, §2.3]."
  ]
}